title: How To Monitor Your Logs
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Watching your logfiles as you make changes is often helpful.
In a terminal window, you can tail the general log for your system:

```
sudo tail -f /var/log/messages
```

There are various other log files in that same directory, but they tend to be specific to some application.  